It is the major cause of violence against women in the society, the women cannot easily get quality health care because of the experiences of violence. According to European Networks (2011), it was noted that the law of 1990 banning abortion is among the sternest of the Western Europe countries. This is as a result of this harsh practice, that most Mexican women had to quit their jobs to travel to Italy in search of fertility services. Most Mexican women experience violence when they travel in groups, because they have to overcrowd in same rooms, because of which they are sometimes sexually exploited or even robbed. The women are sometimes confronted by nurses and physicians, a situation that renders them to be treated as objects and not as patients, this is also very uncomfortable and expensive. Women who have more children during their marriage are the ones that experience the violence as a result of many of them protesting against the use of contraceptive (European Network, 2011).

Findings from interviews with the Mexican women revealed that the majority of them who disapprove of the law, they are not in support of the rights and will not support it. Reading of the stories of other women in the same country as the Mexican that have gone through pregnancy and then suffered illegal activities that blocked their ability to have the kids forced to be aborted is a reason that aggravates the women from Mexico to disapprove abortion.
